@startuml akdb-authority-contexts
title AKDB - Context-Dependent Authority
rectangle "DB-native SAD/UML" as Native
rectangle "Imported external architecture/evidence" as Imported
rectangle "Registered Git provenance" as Git
rectangle "Exported AKDB projection" as Projection
database "AKDB knowledge database" as DB
Native --> DB : canonical authoring record / akdb:// source
Imported --> DB : indexed copy / original source URI retained
Git --> DB : read-only commit/file evidence
DB --> Projection : deterministic export
Projection ..> Native : reviewable snapshot only
note bottom
Authority is not globally "files" or globally "database".
For AKDB-authored SAD/UML the database is source of truth.
For imported material the owning source remains authoritative.
Git metadata is evidence; export files are projections.
end note
@enduml
